 and are there any more seats left in room two B

71
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:45,180
 for that interesting panel?

72
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:46,580
 And then we just keep it going

73
00:02:46,580 --> 00:02:49,060
 because we kind of enjoy talking to each other.

74
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:50,540
 And in this time more than ever,

75
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:52,660
 so those are all sort of back we activate again

76
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:55,300
 and we also have Discord and so on as well.

77
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:58,220
 So the mailing list is actually dying a little bit,

78
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,620
 but I'm not sad because it's been replaced with other things.

79
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:03,900
 - Yeah, and I think I'm on various fan-ish mailing lists.

80
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:07,060
 There is a top secret mailing list full of fan fund winners

81
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:09,420
 and most of that is very good-natured.

82
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:11,380
 That has been a flurry of discussion

83
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:13,460
 in light of recent events,

84
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:16,100
 but we will get to that a bit later in the show.

85
00:03:16,100 --> 00:03:19,740
 Liz mentioned Discord and there is also now a BSFA Discord.

86
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:22,340
 If you are a member of the British Science Fiction Association

87
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,340
 or if you are not,

88
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:25,860
 but you would like to talk to people who are,

89
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:27,060
 you can join their Discord

